import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    zip_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    zip_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'])
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude coordinates?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    city_names = data['city'].values
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=480, height=480, margin=0).generate(' '.join(city_names))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the most common city name in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot_data = data.groupby('state')['longitude'].apply(list)
    plt.boxplot(box_plot_data, vert=True, patch_artist=True)
    plt.xticks(range(1, len(box_plot_data.index) + 1), box_plot_data.index)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of longitude coordinates across different states?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
